item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: sinisakomlenic
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Contemporary design at china 2015 expo
item.dc:creator: sinisakomlenic
item.content:encoded:
[dropcap style="no-background"] S [/dropcap]eptember saw shanghai at centre focus of the global furniture industry with the annual china international furniture (furniture china) expo in full swing<!--more--> — an event which has become one of the most significant trade platforms for the creative sector; offering insights into domestic and overseas economic trends
Successfully pushing China’s most populous city as being an international hub and metropolis of design, the furniture China expo has quickly gained a good reputation at home and abroad for the exhibition of top quality companies and manufacturers on its show floor.

item.title: Minimalist Stool
item.dc:creator: sinisakomlenic
item.content:encoded:
The precise and elegant form of HOCKER HEINRICH’S delicate concrete body is captivating. Smooth outer surfaces stand in complimentary tension to the faceted interior forms.<!--more--> Light and shadow create a game of shifting perspectives depending on the angle of observation.
While concrete furniture has tended towards compact and cubic structures, HOCKER HEINRICH reinterprets the material with a new approach that renders its technical execution a considerable challenge. The stool is hand-made in Berlin. The individual surface structures created during the manufacturing process give each stool a unique appearance, making it a one-of-a-kind. The weatherproof character of concrete also renders the stool suitable for outdoors.

item.title: Equal chair
item.dc:creator: zeljkogudelj
item.content:encoded:
It’s the meeting between industrial strength and nature’s own untameable force that lock the Equal chair together in this unexpected marriage between industrial and traditional craftsmanship.<!--more-->A single screw seals it all off, the ever expanding and retracting wood in the tight grip of a single, seamless piece of cast metal.
Strong relationships between objects – as with people – are often characterized by complete opposites. One parts urge to expand and retract and the stillness and stability of the other. The result is harmony. This is how ash and cast aluminium are united in the Equal chair.

item.title: Carved
item.dc:creator: zeljkogudelj
item.content:encoded:
Inspired by the texture left in a yoghurt while eating it with a spoon , The Carved Bowls are a set of solid wood pin trays that combine with different sized concave areas.<!--more-->
Ideal for the entrance of your home or your desk, you can leave your keys, coins, rings, or your personal items there. The different compartments allow you to separate the different objects by type or to create storage partitions in a shared flat (each member with a different area). The small version works perfectly as a jewelry tray on your bedside table or as a serving dish in restaurants. Produced in close collaboration with a wood turner workshop in Spain, the pieces are hand made using traditional tools and techniques. An innovative point: we used different centers of turning for carving each void. The result was surprisingly beautiful.

item.title: White Square
item.dc:creator: zeljkogudelj
item.content:encoded:
This clock is designed as a minimalistic interior object that can either stand or hang on a wall. The softened square shape in combination with timeless ceramics and contemporary bamboo, gives this clock its subtle character.<!--more-->
But I must explain to you how all this mistaken idea of denouncing pleasure and praising pain was born and I will give you a complete account of the system, and expound the actual teachings of the great explorer of the truth, the master-builder of human happiness. No one rejects, dislikes, or avoids pleasure itself, because it is pleasure, but because those who do not know how to pursue pleasure rationally encounter consequences that are extremely painful. Nor again is there anyone who loves or pursues or desires to obtain pain of itself, because it is pain, but because occasionally circumstances occur in which toil and pain can procure him some great pleasure.

item.title: Trends That Will Stand the Test of Time
item.dc:creator: zeljkogudelj
item.content:encoded:
On the other hand, we denounce with righteous indignation and dislike men who are so beguiled and demoralized by the charms of pleasure of the moment, so blinded by desire, that they cannot foresee the pain and trouble that are bound to ensue;<!--more--> and equal blame belongs to those who fail in their duty through weakness of will, which is the same as saying through shrinking from toil and pain. These cases are perfectly simple and easy to distinguish.
In a free hour, when our power of choice is untrammelled and when nothing prevents our being able to do what we like best, every pleasure is to be welcomed and every pain avoided. But in certain circumstances and owing to the claims of duty or the obligations of business it will frequently occur that pleasures have to be repudiated and annoyances accepted. The wise man therefore always holds in these matters to this principle of selection: he rejects pleasures to secure other greater pleasures, or else he endures pains to avoid worse pains.

item.title: Graeshoppa floor lamp
item.dc:creator: zeljkogudelj
item.content:encoded: Material: Aluminium, Steel Measurements: H: 125.5 cm, W: 43.5 cm, Cord length: 2 m Weight: 2.3 kg Technical information: 1 x max. 40W E14.
item.excerpt:encoded:
One of the most iconic products Greta Grossman designed in the 40's was the Gräshoppa floor lamp.
Grossman was highly influenced by European Modernism, which had been imported to the US by influencial architects, such as Walter Gropius (founder of the Bauhaus) and Ludwig Mies van der Rohe. Grossman, in turn, played a significant role in defining the aesthetic of mid-century Californian Modernism.

item.title: Acorn
item.dc:creator: zeljkogudelj
item.content:encoded:
Shade colour: Matt off–white or matt grey (Pantone Cool Grey 11) Body material: Aluminium and oak

220V - 240V ~ 50Hz Net weight: 2.3 kg
item.excerpt:encoded: Acorn’s streamlined shape was inspired by a natural form, giving it organic contours and an understated profile. The shade resembles the empty shell of an acorn, which becomes hollow once the ripened nut has broken free. Like an acorn’s stem, the top of the shade tapers into a tactile shape.

Its fragmented armrests resemble the line of a human arm folded in the elbow, thus creating almost a crystal form. Its rigorous geometry is softened with paddings, merging the firmness and the gentleness of sitting comfort.
